            <title>[SOLR-1679] SolrCore.execute should wrap log message construction in &quot;if (log.isInfoEnabled())&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1679</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As mentioned by Fuad on solr-user, there is some non-trivial log message construction happening in SolreCore.execute that should be wrapped in &quot;if (log.isInfoEnabled())&quot; ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://old.nabble.com/SOLR-Performance-Tuning%3A-Disable-INFO-Logging.-to26866730.html#a26866943&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://old.nabble.com/SOLR-Performance-Tuning%3A-Disable-INFO-Logging.-to26866730.html#a26866943&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...the warn level message in that same method could probably also be wrapped since it does some large string building as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
